President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania in response to the emergency conditions caused by the remnants of Tropical Storm Lee. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security's Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected counties. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA's news desk.